  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML surrogate)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a neural-network surrogate model of CFD hemolysis prediction for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the ML surrogate can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. A feedforward neural network was trained on 1 200 CFD-generated operating points to predict the relative hemolysis index (RH) across five flow-speed combinations. Two independent training runs (seeds 42 and 137) were executed; both runs achieved mean absolute error below 0.003 RH units on the held-out test set, and the package reports agreement between the two runs as sufficient evidence of reproducibility. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2).",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-rh-criterion",
