      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Underlying CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022R2) verified against manufactured solutions; ML surrogate arithmetic verified via deterministic forward-pass test.",
      "rationale": "CFD solver verification documented in Morrison et al. (2023). ML surrogate numerical correctness confirmed by replaying a fixed mini-batch through the saved model checkpoint and comparing activations to stored reference values; bit-exact match achieved, confirming no numerical drift in the inference path."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD mesh independence demonstrated; ML training-set density sufficient to resolve RH response surface within ±0.005 RH units.",
      "rationale": "CFD mesh independence study performed at three refinement levels (3.2 M, 6.4 M, 12.8 M cells); Richardson extrapolation yields GCI < 1.2% for RH. Training dataset of 1 200 CFD points sampled via Latin hypercube across the 5-dimensional operating space; leave-one-out cross-validation confirms surrogate interpolation error < 0.004 RH units across the domain."
    },
    {
