      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis tests conducted per ASTM F1841 with bovine blood at 37 °C. Measured flow rates and pump speeds logged at 10 Hz; time-averaged values deviate from CFD boundary conditions by at most 3.1% across all 5 operating points. Temperature drift ±0.4 °C; viscosity variation ±2.8% — both within tolerance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "ML surrogate RH predictions agree with in vitro NIH (normalized index of hemolysis) measurements to within ±10% across all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "Surrogate RH predictions converted to NIH via established power-law correlation. Comparison against triplicate in vitro measurements shows maximum deviation of 7.4% at the highest-shear operating point (6 L/min, 3 600 rpm). Mean deviation across all 5 points is 4.1%. Both seed-42 and seed-137 model predictions fall within the ±10% band; the package records this as mutual confirmation of adequacy."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
